obo:GO_0098982  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_4054  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1A: Neuropeptide Y (NPY) induced a sustained increase in spontaneous GABA release from stellate cells in cerebellar slices.\nFigure 1B and C: Application of NPY induced an increase in the frequency of mIPSCs.\nFigure 2A-D: To test if NPY induced increase in the frequency of mIPSCs is mediated via enhanced spontaneous GABA release, GABA A receptor blocker, bicuculline was added. NPY was able to increase the frequency of mIPSC and remained elevated for at least 30 min after application.\n\nThese results suggest that NPY triggers a long-lasting increase in spontaneous GABA release from inhibitory interneurons in cerebellar slices and cultures.. Experimental description: Cerebella of 1-wk-old C57BL/6J mice were dissociated as described previously (Fiszman et al. 2005). Whole-cell patch-clamp recordings were made at 22°C from cultured granule cells in an extracellular solution (in mM: 145 NaCl, 3 KCl, 1 MgCl2, 2 CaCl2, 25 glucose, and 10 HEPES, pH 7.3). Granule cells were identified by their morphological characteristics and lack of spontaneous action potentials in cell-attached mode." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2020-12-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4054" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

